Former Turkish Prime Minister Ahmet Davutolu is a member of Turkish politics and academia. He led the country from 2014 to 2016. From 1999 to 2018, he represented Konya as a member of parliament, and from 2009 to 2014, he served as the country's minister of foreign affairs. His foreign policy of "zero difficulties with neighbors" is well-known for its success in enhancing ties between Turkey and its neighbors. 